<dl id="n12023a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12023a">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12023a"> 23(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <u>Merlin</u> / vocal tombe</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Con questa intenzion prese il cammino / Verse le selve, prossime a Pontiero, / Dove <mark>la vocal tomba di Merlino</mark>. Ce que lui apprit la voix de la tombe, une <i>Revue</i> en cr&eacute;dit le r&eacute;p&eacute;ta &agrave; ses lecteurs, et tout inexp&eacute;riment&eacute; que leur par&ucirc;t l&apos;interpr&egrave;te du barde breton, ils ne d&eacute;daign&egrave;rent pas de l&apos;&eacute;couter <br><font color="green">[With this intention he took to the road / towards the wood, close to Pontiero, / where the vocal tomb of Merlin is. What this voice of the tomb told him, a Review of repute repeated to its reader, and however inexperienced this interpreter of the Breton bard seemed to them, they did not refuse to listen to him]</font> <small> [TLMM]Th&eacute;odore-Claude Hersart, Vicomte de La Villemarqu&eacute;, <cite a>Myrdhinn, ou l'enchanteur Merlin</cite></a> (1862) IV</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
